  "text": "In brief, we randomised 130 healthy (blood pressure < 140/90 mmHg; fasting blood glucose < 6.1 mmol/l; no regular use of medication), sedentary (regular exercise < 2 hours/week and active commuting <5 km/day; VO 2 peak: women < 40 ml O 2 /kg/min and men < 45 ml O 2 /kg/min), young (20-45 years), nonsmoking, Caucasian women and men who are overweight/obese (class 1) (BMI 25-35 kg/m 2 ; fat percentage: women ≥ 32% and men ≥ 25%). Exclusion criteria included abnormal resting electrocardiogram and parents or siblings with type 2 diabetes, and for women, they include postmenopause, pregnancy, or planned pregnancy [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
